This paper is about salient object detection using deep learning techniques, specifically Fully Convolutional Neural Networks (FCNs) and the Holistically-Nested Edge Detector (HED). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep supervision and short connections, which are common techniques in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the efficiency of the proposed method, which could fall under the category of neural networks and learning (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM).
